Swastika (Auspicious symbol in Hindu culture)

Swastik is very sacred symbol for Hindus and it represent peace, luck, hope, harmony and prosperity. 

It is considered as the symbol of God Shree Ganesha, Lord Vishnu and the seat of the sun.

Lets all pray for all of us, well-being for all and hope we pass 2020 without any other sad news.

Lets pray and hope for good luck for all and come out of these hard times safe and secure

✨6 Hip Mobility Drills✨

🔆Reminders:
•Don’t force yourself into any movement.
•Work within your current range of motion.
•Gradually increase the depth or intensity over time.

⸻

🔸 1. Internal & External Hip Rotation
•Keep the hips grounded — don’t lift them.
•Move only the leg, rotating it inward and outward.

🔸 2. 90/90 Heel Lift
•Front shin at a right angle (90°).
•Back knee and foot in one straight line.
•You can place Hands on the floor for support — lift the back heel only. 

🔶 3. Malasana Internal Rotation
•As you rotate one leg inward, keep the opposite heel grounded.

🔸 4. Hip Controlled Articular Rotations (CARs)
•Stay tall — no leaning or collapsing.
•Keep arms straight and avoid shifting your weight.

🔸 5. Hip Flexor Stretch
•Front knee aligned over the ankle.
•Square the pelvis — back thigh points toward the floor.
•Core Engage

🔸 6. Stretching Lizard
•Front knee stacked over ankle.
•Push the hips down and gently press the front leg outward.
•Breathe steadily.
